  "prompt": "How does UPS Next Day Air works?",
  "response": "UPS Next Day Air is a premium shipping service that guarantees delivery of packages by the next business day. Here's how it works:\n\n1. Shipping Options\n- Packages are guaranteed to be delivered by 10:30 AM or 3 PM the next business day\n- Available for both domestic and international shipments\n- Delivery time depends on origin and destination locations\n\n2. Shipping Process\n- Packages are picked up from the sender's location\n- Transported via air transportation\n- Processed through UPS sorting facilities\n- Delivered directly to the recipient's address\n\n3. Key Features\n- Fastest UPS shipping option\n- Ideal for urgent or time-sensitive shipments\n- Can be tracked online in real-time\n- Provides proof of delivery\n- Higher cost compared to standard shipping methods\n\n4. Restrictions\n- Weight and size limitations apply\n- Some remote or rural locations might have limited service\n- Delivery times might vary during holidays or peak shipping seasons\n\n5. Pricing\n- Cost depends on package weight, dimensions, and delivery distance\n- Typically more expensive than standard ground shipping\n- Rates can be calculated on UPS website or at local UPS store\n\nCustomers can book and schedule Next Day Air shipments online, by phone, or at a UPS location.",
